raph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"24px\"}},\"textColor\":\"white\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"has-white-color has-text-color\" style=\"font-size:24px\">Finding a boat:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We thought the price was really expensive just before Covid, but we were up for a surprise when we saw the price go up during the pandemic ð·. We looked at a super cheap project boat around NYC, but this also mean all weekend doing fiberglass job in a boatyard instead of enjoying it. At this point we had 2 diverging options, go all in into a bigger project boat (hurricane damaged, badly maintained, etcâ¦) and dump a lot of time into it, OR keep working into high paying job and just buy a well maintained boat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Scouting for boat into âexotics?â places.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul>
<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Puerto Rico</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>US Virgin Islands</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Croatia 2x</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Florida (keys)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Greece<br>Every occasion is good to look for what is out there and how marina works.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->
</ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"24px\"}}} -->\n<h2 style=\"font-size:24px\">The patterns we found:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Boat in the USA are about 1.5x more expensive than boat in the Mediterranean.<br>There is a lot more boat in the Med than US/Caribbean.<br>Boat in the Caribbean gets cheaper around summer (June-Sept) to avoid hiding the boat for the hurricane season.<br>Boat in the Mediterranean are cheaper between September-December to avoid Haul-out cost &amp; for company to rotate the stocks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"24px\"}}} -->\n<h2 style=\"font-size:24px\">So...?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On a cold night in the hot tub in Daytona beach the subject came back to âOh I wonder what is out there nowâ, so we looked for fun. We were not expecting to find anything since it\'s supposed to be the low season for selling boat, and all the good boat that were cheap as a bargain would be already gone by October. But we found a Hanse 41 for 74k (Euro) in Greece, It was a good price since most boat we looked at were ~100-150k So even if we would give a bit of love it should still work. The same idea as our house, the foundation need to be good. So we can fix small details but any structural damaged we are out (specially for the first time owner). So for the first time we contacted the agent and started to talk and see what was a process we might do a whole blog about what the processes later. But basically they wanted us to do the inspection of the boat before we even put an offer, in so we schedule everything and because we half crazy and flexible, {{AUTHOR_CESINE}} decided to be present for the inspection of the boat increase the next week. With the limited info from the agent and a few outside picture, Crazy details oriented {{AUTHOR_CESINE}} was able to find details like hill behind t