<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Offer</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Inspection/haulout</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Sign the contract from the seller</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Sign contract from Buyer</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Send paperwork to France to eradicate from the registry</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Wait for eradication</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Register boat back</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Sailing into the sunset</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->
</ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Usually, the boat would be in a dry dock until the completion of the process and once everything is done we take it and sail away. But this one was on anchor and we did not understand the full process as first-time owners of a boat.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"22px\"}}} -->\n<h2 style=\"font-size:22px\">Sitting dock</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We made an offer around February, made the inspection on March 10 and were supposed to take possession on May 1 just in time for the summer!!!&nbsp; As young(ish) excited people, we were rushing everything and we tough that from May-1 we would have all the paperwork to register the boat. BUTâ¦ we jumped a few steps as usual. So we arrived at the boat with a few boxes expecting âto move inâ then we would register and within 1 week we would be out sailing. The Dreamâ¦</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":163,\"width\":768,\"height\":576,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\">
